This paper combines deep reinforcement learning with symbolic planning, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper deals with deep reinforcement learning, which is a popular subfield of AI. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since deep reinforcement learning is a type of machine learning. The third likely category is cs.RO (Robotics) since the paper discusses hierarchical decision-making, which is a common topic in robotics. The fourth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control) since the paper deals with control of subtasks. The fifth likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages) since the paper introduces a framework that involves symbolic planning.
